EXIT:0

docket — OpenClaw project manager

AGENT TYPES
  Org Specialists     Created by 'docket install' — shared across all projects
                        → manager, knowledge, security
                        → Work across ALL projects (don't create/delete manually)
  Project Pods        Created by 'docket add' — one isolated pod per project
                        → lead + implementer (+ optional reviewer, tester)
                        → Manage with 'docket pod <project>'

  Project Agents      Created by 'docket add' — one per project/codebase
                        → Each has its own workspace, memory, and Telegram group

USAGE
  docket [--debug] <command> [agent-id] [args]
  If agent-id is omitted an interactive picker is shown (fzf or numbered list).

SETUP
  install            Bootstrap OpenClaw + create specialist agents

LIFECYCLE
  list               List all project agents and their status
  add                Add a new project agent (interactive)
  add --from <f>     Provision agent(s) from a YAML/JSON spec (declarative)
  info     [id]      Detailed status for a project
  delete   [id]      Remove a project agent
  maintain [id]      Health check & maintenance (see subcommands below)

MAINTENANCE  (docket maintain [id] <subcommand>)
  check              Health check + auto-fix (default)
  clean              Clear memory logs only
  reset              Clear memory + heartbeat
  rebuild            Deep rebuild from .docket-meta.json
  sessions           Archive large/old sessions (>5 MB or >30 days)

TELEGRAM
  wire   [id]        Wire or update a Telegram group binding
  unwire [id]        Remove Telegram binding from a project

CONFIGURATION
  profile  [id] [m]  Pin an agent's model (<provider/model>) or 'default' to
                        follow the role policy; --budget <USD> sets a spending cap
  models             View/change the role→model policy; switch provider presets
  scope    [id] [a]  Manage session scopes for multi-project isolation
  auth     <action>  Configure Claude model auth (subscription or API key)
  keys     <action>  Manage workspace secrets — syncs to all agents

CONTEXT & MEMORY  (docket context [id] <subcommand>)
  show               Recent activity, active tasks, stats (default)
  search  <query>    Search indexed memory
  snapshot           Create SNAPSHOT.md for fast agent context
  index              Index memory files for search
  compress           Archive logs older than 30 days
  project            Quick-reference: codebase, stack, decisions

MONITORING
  cost     [id]      Token usage and cost breakdown with budget status
  doctor             System health: gateway, config, drift, budget, runaway
  gates              Exec-approval gates: status / enable / disable (opt-in)
  audit    [N]       Recent mutating operations (keys, gates, profile, agents)
  eval               Specialist-role evals: structural checks + live golden tasks

OBSERVABILITY (Phase 8)
  trace    <session>  Render one agent-action trace human-readable
  trace tail <proj>   Follow the most-recent session live
  trace export <proj> Export raw JSONL (--since YYYY-MM-DD)
  trace ingest <proj> Ingest daemon session logs into traces
  metrics            Success rate, latency, cost, guardrail trips (--role --window)
  policies list      List installed guardrail policies
  policies init      Install baseline policies (block-destructive, injection, redact)
  policies test      Dry-run policy evaluator on any text
  approve  <token>   Grant a pending HITL approval
  deny     <token>   Deny a pending HITL approval

PODS, QUEUE & WORKFLOWS
  pod <project>      Inspect/manage a project pod (add/remove members)
  team delegate      Queue a task for the org manager agent
  team queue         Show pending manager tasks
  team done          Mark a task as complete
  workflow [id]      Manage Lobster YAML pipelines

UTILITIES
  logs      [id]     View memory logs and gateway entries
  edit      [id]     Open workspace files in $EDITOR
  snapshot           JSON dump of all agents, bindings, costs (--output <file>)
  serve              Live JSON endpoint for dashboards (--port 7331 --interval 30)
  completions        Shell completion script — eval "$(docket completions bash|zsh)"
  help               This help message

MODEL POLICY  (default: Anthropic — change with 'docket models preset')
  Each agent role maps to the cheapest adequate model:
  cheap   anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5   manager reviewer tester knowledge task
  strong  anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6  programmer security repo
  'docket models' shows the full role→model table with pricing; 'docket profile <id>'
  pins one agent to any model (incl. opus-class) without changing the policy.

FLAGS
  --debug         Verbose mode — or set DEBUG=1 in env

EXAMPLES
  docket                            # show project list
  docket add                        # add a new project (interactive)
  docket add --from agents.yaml     # provision a fleet from a spec file
  docket doctor                     # full health check
  docket info myproject             # inspect one project
  docket maintain myproject clean   # clear memory logs
  docket profile myproject default  # follow the role policy model
  docket profile myproject anthropic/claude-opus-4-6  # pin a stronger model
  docket profile myproject --budget 5  # set $5 spending cap
  docket context myproject search "auth bug"  # search memory
  docket cost                       # cost breakdown for all agents
  docket team delegate "Fix login bug"  # queue task for manager
  docket team queue                 # show pending tasks

PATHS
  Workspaces:  ~/.openclaw/workspaces/projects/
  Config:      ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json
  Logs:        <TMP>

